    "B Examples of alternative promptsIn the following, we present a running example of a specific window and how it is processed by the alternative prompts considered in this paper.",
    "Figure 1 show the states of this window.",
    "Note that the presence in the kitchen and cutlery drawer are \"already active\" and \"persistent\" states, the first segment of the fridge is an \"already active\" state, while the second segment of the fridge is an \"inner\" state.",
    "B.1 ADL-LLM Here we show how the window in Figure 1 is handled by the approach proposed in our paper.",
    "B.1.1 System prompt."
